            "source": "Cointelegraph",
            "source_type": "news",
            "summary": "XRP experienced a rally between Oct. 25, 2024, and Jan. 16, 2025, gaining 600% due to hopes of a favorable crypto presidency, hitting a 7-year high. However, speculation surrounding XRP has since declined, leading to increasing losses for holders. XRP daily active addresses rose by 490%, reaching a 7-year high. Retail confidence in XRP is waning, with new investors holding 62.8% of realized cap. Since late February 2025, capital inflows have decreased, with whale addresses offloading over $1 billion in positions. XRP has found support at $2 but may drop below it. A bullish divergence is observed in the 1-hour and 4-hour charts, with a bearish outlook on the higher timeframe. XRP may find support at the 200-day moving average. This article does not offer investment advice.",
